text: This is the BBC. This podcast is supported by Advertising outside the UK. BBC Learning English let's learn the verb identify. If you identify something or someone, it means you notice it or them and can say who or what they are. I identified the person in the photo as my neighbor. There was a flavour in this soup that I just couldn't identify. If you identify with someone or a group of people, then you feel that you have something in common with them. I can identify with your problems. I have similar ones. If you identify as something, it means you would label yourself in that way. I identify as a hard worker. I'm proud of what I do. Identify is about recognition. It can be about recognizing people and things. You can identify with a situation you recognize. And if you identify as something, it's how you see yourself. You're listening to bbclearningenglish.com.
